# XLN Architecture (Manual)

**Activate when working on XLN protocol code**

## Core Model
```
Server → Signer → Entity → Account
```

## Entity Types
- Single-signer: Auto-approved blocks (instant)
- Multi-signer: 2/3+ quorum required
- Hub: Orderbook + cross-jurisdictional swaps

## Key Concepts
- No global consensus (entities independent)
- 100ms block time per entity
- HTLC for cross-chain swaps with 8-bit granulation
- Credit lines > collateral deposits
- State = consensus agreed, Storage = full machine data

## Message Flow
```
Mempool → Block Creation → Consensus → Execution
Outbox → Server routes → EntityInput → Apply
```

## Implementation Patterns
- Server: @src/core/server.ts
- Entity commands: @src/core/entity/commands.ts  
- Consensus: @src/core/consensus.ts
- Protocols: @src/protocols/wallet.ts
- Storage: @src/storage/memory.ts

## Swap Architecture
Hub locks B-tokens first → Alice mirrors A-tokens → Simultaneous reveal
